precept ShiftSchedule# A clinic schedules staff shifts. Each shift has a start time filed as# an instant (UTC). The clinic operates in a specific timezone, and# scheduling rules depend on the local date and local time of day.## SYNTAX STYLE: dot accessor form — field.inZone(timezone)field ClinicTimezone as timezone default 'America/New_York'field ShiftStart as instantfield ShiftLocalDateTime as localdatetimefield ShiftLocalDate as localdatefield ShiftLocalTime as localtimefield StaffName as string nullablefield IsOvernight as boolean default falseinvariant ShiftLocalTime >= '06:00' or IsOvernight    because "Non-overnight shifts cannot start before 6 AM local time"invariant ShiftLocalDate.dayOfWeek != 'Sunday' or StaffName != null    because "Sunday shifts must have a staff assignment"state Unscheduled initialstate Scheduledstate Confirmedstate Completedin Scheduled write StaffNameevent ScheduleShift with Start as instantevent AssignStaff with Name as stringon AssignStaff assert Name != "" because "Staff name is required"event ConfirmShiftevent CompleteShiftfrom Unscheduled on ScheduleShift    -> set ShiftStart = ScheduleShift.Start    -> set ShiftLocalDateTime = ScheduleShift.Start.inZone(ClinicTimezone).localdatetime    -> set ShiftLocalDate = ScheduleShift.Start.inZone(ClinicTimezone).localdate    -> set ShiftLocalTime = ScheduleShift.Start.inZone(ClinicTimezone).localtime    -> set IsOvernight = ScheduleShift.Start.inZone(ClinicTimezone).localtime >= '22:00'    -> transition Scheduledfrom Scheduled on AssignStaff    -> set StaffName = AssignStaff.Name    -> no transitionfrom Scheduled on ConfirmShift when StaffName != null    -> transition Confirmedfrom Confirmed on CompleteShift    -> transition Completed